During the day, only the image of the Presidential Meeting was transmitted in the pressroom with the message "private meeting, limited audio".
The few information circulated among journalists was received by the press speakers from some of the governments of the Unasur meeting, but not by the Peruvian press speaker.
The only document that was distributed during the day was the list of participating presidents, which led to the dissatisfaction of hundreds of journalists from various national and international media, who demanded more information.
After that, Peru's president sent the media an e-mail with the "final statement" of the summit, but it was the statement of Humala and not the official document for the conclusion of the summit.
Last October, Peru was the host of the IIIrd South American Summit (ASPA), and even on this occasion, despite a strong call from the press, the so-called statement by Lima, which had been announced earlier, was not published.
On the official website of the ASPA you can be sure that the document was published last Tuesday.
